**Answer: (C) Perfect diamagnet with χ = −1 and μᵣ = 0**

\text{Superconductors exhibit the Meissner effect:}
\text{they expel all magnetic flux from their interior.}

\text{Inside superconductor: } B = 0

\text{Since } B = \mu_0(H + M) = 0 \Rightarrow M = -H

\text{Susceptibility: } \chi = M/H = -1 \text{ (perfect diamagnet)}

\text{Permeability: } \mu_r = 1 + \chi = 1 + (-1) = 0

\text{This is the most extreme possible diamagnetic response.}

